pageContext.claim: “The numbers are getting to a point where they can [reopen states], and there just seems to be no effort on certain blue states to get back into gear.”
pageContext.analysis: On the contrary, Democratic governors in many if not all states have drawn up plans for reopening -- largely following the White House's guidelines -- though they have tended to be more cautious than some Republican governors. It's worth noting that by happenstance Democrats hold the governorship in some of the states with the biggest outbreaks such as California, New Jersey and New York.
